                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 7.  <span><em> MiR-10</em> acts in synergy with <em>HoxB4.</em></span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec6.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec6.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>A) Embryos injected with <em>HoxB4</em>, <em>miR-10</em> siRNA and <em>HoxB4</em>+<em>miR-10</em> siRNA analyzed for the expression of <em>HoxB1a</em> and <em>HoxB3a</em> at 24 hpf. Injection of 150pg <em>HoxB4</em> leads to downregulation of <em>HoxB1a</em> and of downregulation of the hindbrain domain of <em>HoxB3a</em>. The rhombomere 4 expression domain of <em>HoxB1a</em> and the rhombomere 5/6 expression domain of <em>HoxB3a</em> are still discernable though. When 150pg <em>HoxB4</em> is expressed together with <em>miR-10</em> siRNA the expression domain of <em>HoxB1a</em> disappears and no clear rhombomere 5/6 stripe of <em>HoxB3a</em> expression can be detected. B) Embryos injected with <em>HoxB4</em>, <em>miR-10</em> siRNA and <em>HoxB4</em>+<em>miR-10</em> siRNA analyzed for the expression of endogenous <em>HoxB4a</em> at 48 hpf. The combination of <em>HoxB4</em> together with the <em>miR-10</em> siRNA induces a stronger phenotype with more severe anterior and posterior truncations than injection with <em>HoxB4</em> alone. On the right groups of embryos injected with <em>HoxB4</em> or the combination of <em>HoxB4</em> and <em>miR-10</em> siRNA are shown.</p>
